<subSubSection id="DE86AF94FFF9FFD5FF43562AE8CE2CAF" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9623FC1FFFF9FFD5FF43562AE8CE2CAF" blockId="5.[151,1436,1250,1524]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="A4E8200DFFF9FFD5FF43562AE8222C04" bold="true" box="[199,315,1356,1380]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="519C879CFFF9FFD5FEC5562AEB122C04" box="[321,523,1356,1380]" class="Arachnida" family="Axonopsidae" genus="Axonopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis id="A4E8200DFFF9FFD5FEC5562AEB122C04" box="[321,523,1356,1380]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">Axonopsis serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the spine–like projections on the dorsal shield (
<figureCitation id="0EA7E09AFFF9FFD5FB72562AEC562C04" box="[1270,1359,1356,1380]" captionStart="FIGURE 4 A – G" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1821,1844]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,343,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,337,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4 A – G. Axonopsis (Hexaxonopsis) serrata Walter, 1928, (A – C = female, D – G = male): A = idiosoma, dorsal view; B = idiosoma, ventral view; C = I-L- 4 - 6; D = idiosoma, ventral view; E = genital field; F = palp, lateral view; G = IV-L- 1 - 6. Scale bars = 100 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204458/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">
Fig. 
<number id="2054EE38FFF9FFD5FAAD562AEC212C04" box="[1321,1336,1356,1380]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" value="4.0">4</number>
A
</figureCitation>
), more spine-like processes associated with the first and second coxae (
<figureCitation id="0EA7E09AFFF9FFD5FCE15609EAC62CE7" box="[869,991,1391,1415]" captionStart="FIGURE 4 A – G" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1821,1844]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,343,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,337,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4 A – G. Axonopsis (Hexaxonopsis) serrata Walter, 1928, (A – C = female, D – G = male): A = idiosoma, dorsal view; B = idiosoma, ventral view; C = I-L- 4 - 6; D = idiosoma, ventral view; E = genital field; F = palp, lateral view; G = IV-L- 1 - 6. Scale bars = 100 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204458/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">
Fig. 
<number id="2054EE38FFF9FFD5FC1D5609EAB12CE7" box="[921,936,1391,1415]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" value="4.0">4</number>
B–D
</figureCitation>
), a small projections on the lateral margins of the ventral shield (
<figureCitation id="0EA7E09AFFF9FFD5FE4756F2EB242CCC" box="[451,573,1428,1452]" captionStart="FIGURE 4 A – G" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1821,1844]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,343,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,337,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4 A – G. Axonopsis (Hexaxonopsis) serrata Walter, 1928, (A – C = female, D – G = male): A = idiosoma, dorsal view; B = idiosoma, ventral view; C = I-L- 4 - 6; D = idiosoma, ventral view; E = genital field; F = palp, lateral view; G = IV-L- 1 - 6. Scale bars = 100 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204458/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">
Fig. 
<number id="2054EE38FFF9FFD5FE7D56F2EB1E2CCC" box="[505,519,1428,1452]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" value="4.0">4</number>
B–D
</figureCitation>
) (see 
<bibRefCitation id="F20D81EEFFF9FFD5FD0756F2EA092CCC" author="Walter" box="[643,784,1428,1452]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" refString="Walter, C. (1928) Hydracariens de l`Algerie et de la Tunisie. (Collections de M. H. Gauthier) (Deuxieme liste). Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de l'Afrique du Nord, Alger, 19, 280 - 336." type="journal article" year="1928">
Walter 
<number id="2054EE38FFF9FFD5FD5156F2EA092CCC" box="[725,784,1428,1452]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" value="1928.0">1928</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F20D81EEFFF9FFD5FC9956F2EAD32CCC" author="Lundblad" box="[797,970,1428,1452]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" refString="Lundblad, O. (1956) Zur Kenntnis sud- und mitteleuropaischer Hydrachnellen. Arkiv for Zoologi, 10 (1), 1 - 306." type="journal article" year="1956">
Lundblad 
<number id="2054EE38FFF9FFD5FC1456F2EAD32CCC" box="[912,970,1428,1452]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" value="1956.0">1956</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and the presence of a heavy seta on the ventral side of P- 
<number id="2054EE38FFF9FFD5FED356D1E87C2CAF" box="[343,357,1463,1487]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" value="4.0">4</number>
(
<figureCitation id="0EA7E09AFFF9FFD5FEF056D1E8D32CAF" box="[372,458,1463,1487]" captionStart="FIGURE 4 A – G" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1821,1844]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,343,1794]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,337,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4 A – G. Axonopsis (Hexaxonopsis) serrata Walter, 1928, (A – C = female, D – G = male): A = idiosoma, dorsal view; B = idiosoma, ventral view; C = I-L- 4 - 6; D = idiosoma, ventral view; E = genital field; F = palp, lateral view; G = IV-L- 1 - 6. Scale bars = 100 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204458/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">
Fig. 
<number id="2054EE38FFF9FFD5FE2D56D1E8A12CAF" box="[425,440,1463,1487]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" value="4.0">4</number>
F
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
